The paper focuses on kinship verification using deep learning techniques and video frames, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The proposed Supervised Mixed Norm AutoEncoder (SMNAE) introduces class-specific sparsity in the weight matrix, which is a machine learning technique and falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
